{
  "doc_id": "50442",
  "text": "Apart from these problems, it is somewhat disappointing to introduce the reference metric as an 'absolute element', i.e., a non-dynamical field in the theory. From this point of view, bimetric (or more general multi-metric) theories, where also the reference metric is dynamical are better motivated [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Interesting discussions about theoretical aspects of bimetric massive gravity can be found in [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] .",
